cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE 

This paper deals with machine translation and specifically focuses on improving the quality of translation through the use of part-of-speech tagging and stemming. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language) which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also involves information retrieval (IR) techniques such as stemming. Hence, cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is the second likely category. The use of machine learning algorithms for improving translation quality suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, since the paper deals with improving the efficiency of machine translation, it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
